We're seeing what appears to be the same issue that was outlined in HIVE-15388 where the query parser spends a lot of time (never returns and I need to kill the beeline process) parsing a command with a lot of "(" .   I tried this in both 2.2 and now 2.3.

Here's an example query (this is auto generated SQL BTW) in beeline that never completes/parses, I end up just killing the beeline process.....

It looks like something similar was addressed as part of HIVE-15388.   Any ideas on how to address this?  write better SQL? patch?

Regards,

Dano
